cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is about learning spatiotemporal features using ConvNets, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the architecture search process, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed architecture on video datasets, which falls under multimedia (cs.MM). The use of deep learning and neural networks also suggests the possibility of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE) sub-categories.
